        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer193247519" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2366389029376310925">The Dragons in Our Midst series is really awesome. I loved the first book to peices. But I don&apos;t really like this book as much as the first one. Why? Because I didn&apos;t like the story line and there wasn&apos;t as much excitement and suspence. The beginning of the book is good the ending is good and the middle is... ehhh. And so I wasn&apos;t very motivated to keep reading. I&apos;m hopping the next book, Circles of Seven, is better and a more exciting read. <br/> <br/> <br/> <br/>Bonnie is going to be adopted by Walter’s parents. </span>
  <span id="freeText2366389029376310925" style="display:none">The Dragons in Our Midst series is really awesome. I loved the first book to peices. But I don't really like this book as much as the first one. Why? Because I didn't like the story line and there wasn't as much excitement and suspence. The beginning of the book is good the ending is good and the middle is... ehhh. And so I wasn't very motivated to keep reading. I'm hopping the next book, Circles of Seven, is better and a more exciting read. <br /> <br /> <br /> <br />Bonnie is going to be adopted by Walter’s parents. But the night before Bonnie’s dad, Dr. Connor comes back for her and claims custody. Bonnie goes back with Dr. Connor after he tells her that her mother isn’t really dead. Billy later finds out that Dr. Connor was lying and sets out to find Bonnie and rescue her. Meanwhile, Dr Connor brings Bonnie back to his secret lab. Dr. Connor wants Bonnie to go into the Candel Stone, telling her that her mother is inside of it. Bonnie goes in only to realize her father had other purposes for her going in.<br /> <br /> <br /> <br />GOOD<br />******<br />Wonderful writting. The charicters are even more developed in this next book. Also new charicters were added. Had good suspence and action at the beginning and ending. Has Christian references all throughout the book which I always find refreshing.<br /> <br /> <br /> <br />BAD<br />****<br />Not much action in the middle of the book. So I got bored.<br /> <br /> <br /> <br />I rated this book G<br /> <br />Written for middleschool age and up but younger kids could read and enjoy just as much. This book is clean and appropriate for all ages.<br /></span>
